We, Concerned Citizens Of Tennessee - Queer Folks and Allies; Parents; Business Owners; Artists; People of Faith and Atheists - have put together this shirt to raise money for @Nashvillelaunchpad a local non-profit supporting unhoused teens in Nashville. LaunchPad focusses on providing affirming care to LGBTQ+ teens, who are at a much higher risk of being unhoused.
.
Link in Bio For Presale!
.
We stand with the Drag Community. Drag is an art-form that has been around for centuries. While we are aware that this shirt will not change legislation, we believe it is a just response to the ridiculous drumming up of a fake cultural emergency.
.
100% of the profits from sales of this shirt will go to @nashvillelaunchpad in their work actually protecting at-risk children in Nashville, as opposed to grandstanding, hateful legislation that does the exact opposite.

Let’s continue to help the Concerned Citizens of TN raise money for @nashvillelaunchpad 
.
Spread the word more!!! They have 700 more orders to hit their goal! Love you all!

We, the Concerned Citizens of Tennessee are 158 orders away from 2,000!! We are raising funds for @nashvillelaunchpad and with supporters like you, we have raised so much money! Share this post or any of the others and purchase via the link in my bio.
